title: MALDIVES TRAVEL VLOG: Snorkeling, Dolphin Cruise, Water Villa Tour & More! 🏝️☀️ | Ep 1
description:
I spent a week in the Maldives exploring 5 different Sun Siyam resorts and having some of the most incredible and luxurious experiences. In this vlog, I fly from Bangalore to Male in the Maldives, take a speedboat from the airport to Sun Siyam Olhuveli Resort, give you a tour of my water villa in the Maldives, go snorkeling, kayaking, see tons of dolphins (I've literally never seen so many dolphins at once) on a sunset cruise, and a lot more! Hope you enjoy this travel vlog from the Maldives :)

Resort: Sun Siyam Olhuveli
You can book this package through GT Holidays: https://www.gtholidays.in (reach out to them at 9940882200)

description:
Join my FREE YouTube Masterclass: https://bit.ly/38dS4o6
Check out my store: https://www.kritikagoelshop.com

Hey everyone! This is the last video from my Sikkim series and it’s all about Gangtok! Since this was my second time in Gangtok, I tried to cover more off beat places that I hadn’t already seen. In this video, I visited some sightseeing spots like Tashi View Point, Ganeshtok, MG Marg, Enchey Monastery and tried some delicious food at Nor-khill hotel and the cute cafes at MG Marg. We also went on a cable card ride to get an amazing view of Gangtok. This was such a perfect way to end my trip to Sikkim! :)

title: I visited 16 countries in 2022! #TravelShorts
description:
If I could relive a year of my life over and over again Groundhog Day style, I’d probably pick 2022. What an incredible year filled with so many new experiences, adventures, fun, love and lots of learnings! So so grateful to 2022 for being the highlight of my whole life. Also can’t believe I traveled to 16 countries (and some of them multiple times like Switzerland Germany and the US); that’s actually more than the number of countries I’d been to all my life prior to 2022. 🤯 Never imagined I’d live a life like this but thank you for making that happen through your support, it literally means the world to me 🥹❤️
Here’s hoping 2023 is as amazing as 2022 was. Happy New Year everyone! 🥳🫶🏻

#TravelShorts #Shorts #2022recap #travel #indiantraveller

description:

title: SIKKIM TRAVEL VLOG | Bagdogra to Gangtok - Vlog #1 | North East India | Kritika Goel
description:
Join my FREE YouTube Masterclass: https://bit.ly/38dS4o6
Check out my store: https://www.kritikagoelshop.com

Hey everyone! I recently went on a trip to Sikkim with my friend Shumnima (who is from Sikkim). During our trip to Sikkim, we explored Gangtok and the western parts of Sikkim (Pelling and around). Although I’ve been to Sikkim before, this trip was such a different experience, especially since I stayed and explored with a local.

This is the first video in my four part series of Sikkim. In this video, we travel from Mumbai to Bagdogra to Gangtok in Sikkim. We also went to MG Marg in Gangtok and I tried some delicious local Sikkimese food! Keep an eye out for the next part of this series where I explore Pelling and West Sikkim.

description:
Join my FREE YouTube Masterclass: https://bit.ly/38dS4o6
Check out my store: https://www.kritikagoelshop.com

title: FIRST CLASS ON SWITZERLAND'S MOST LUXURIOUS & EXPENSIVE TRAIN (Glacier Express)!
description:
The Glacier Express is known as Switzerland's most luxurious and one of its most expensive train rides. I went on the first class Glacier Express from Zermatt to St. Moritz in the month of February and this luxury train ride through the Swiss Alps was one of the most beautiful train journeys I have ever experienced, and not just in Switzerland. If you’re wondering ‘Is the Glacier Express worth it?’, then hopefully this video will answer your question. The Glacier Express is an 8-hour train journey from Zermatt to St. Moritz in Switzerland. It covers some of the most scenic landscapes in Switzerland covering Chur, Andermatt, and the famous bridges around Chur like the Landwasser Viaduct. It’s a beautiful and luxurious experience (the most expensive train ride in Switzerland), but worth every penny! I also talk about how much the Glacier Express costs and a way to do the Glacier Express in a more cost-effective manner. Even though I went on the Glacier Express solo, I actually turned out to be such an amazing experience. I also spent the rest of the evening in snowy St. Moritz. Hope you enjoy this vlog of the Glacier Express! :)

Glacier Express train: https://www.glacierexpress.ch/en

description:
Bonjour from Paris! I'm on a one month long solo trip in Europe, and I'm starting my solo trip with Paris in France! Here's how I spent my first day in Paris, walking around the city and exploring the popular attractions. I had some nice coffee in a Parisian cafe, figured out the metro in Paris, walked down Champs Elysees, saw the Arc de Triomphe, Galeries Lafayette and all the Christmas decoration there plus a stunning view of the Eiffel Tower from the roof, walked by the Seine, The Louvre and of course the Eiffel Tower from up close! This was such a great first day in Paris and I'm already in love with this city! Excited to be traveling solo in Paris and in Europe!

title: SINGAPORE VLOG ✨ Indian Girl Traveling Solo in Singapore | Kritika Goel
description:
Join my FREE YouTube Masterclass: https://bit.ly/38dS4o6
Check out my store: https://www.kritikagoelshop.com
Recently went on a solo trip to Singapore for three days and here’s a vlog about everything I did there!
Booked flights on WEGO: https://wegotravel.onelink.me/cYro/CheapestFlightsxHotels 

This was actually my first proper solo trip abroad (not counting Bali since I spent most days there with a group), and I had such a blast chilling by myself (my second time visiting Singapore though)! I stayed at Boat Quay, which was quite a nice area and was right by the Singapore river. This vlog is from my first two days there where I explore downtown Singapore, see the laser show at Marina Bay Sands, check out the Merlion, Gardens by the Bay, the light and sound show there, and Haji Lane (which is truly a hidden gem) where I tried the famous selfie coffee and also indulged in a bit of shopping!

title: EXPLORING THINNAKARA ISLAND, LAKSHADWEEP | Most Beautiful Beach in India?! | Ep 3
description:
Hello from Lakshadweep! Here’s vlog 3 of my 4 part travel series covering the beautiful islands of Lakshadweep. In this video, I explore the island of Thinnakara in Lakshadweep, which is honestly one of the most beautiful and untouched islands I've been to with the clearest blue waters, visiting a gorgeous sandbank on Bangaram, kayaking on the island and do other fun stuff on the island of Bangaram, Lakshadweep! Also in case you're wondering, I visited Lakshadweep between 11th and 14th October.

title: MY LASIK SURGERY EXPERIENCE // Everything You Need To Know About LASIK Eye Surgery // Kritika Goel
description:
Join my FREE YouTube Masterclass: https://bit.ly/38dS4o6
Check out my store: https://www.kritikagoelshop.com
Hey guys! In this video, I take you through my experience with LASIK Eye surgery before, during, and after the procedure. I share with you everything I know about LASIK and I hope you find this video useful! 😊 Don’t forget to like this video and subscribe to my channel. ❤️

I got LASIK done at Shroff Eye Centre, Kailash Colony, Delhi and my doctor was Dr. Dariel Mathur. If you’re considering getting LASIK done, I would recommend doing your own research and consulting a doctor because everyone’s eyes are different.

A couple of things I forgot to mention in the video: You can’t wear eye make up or get threading done for your eyebrows for an entire month after the surgery.

title: CORDELIA CRUISES TRAVEL VLOG: Chennai to Vizag | Things to Know! 5 Nights on a Cruise in India!
description:
I went on a 5-night cruise vacation from Chennai to Vizag to Pondicherry and back with my entire family & here's what my experience on Cordelia Cruises was like! It's so cool to see a premium cruise in India, and we had a great time enjoying all the good food, the shows, the view of the ocean and the great music. We sailed on The Empress by Cordelia Cruises, which is now on the east coast of India sailing between Chennai, Vizag and Pondicherry. In this vlog, I give you a tour of my room in the cruise, show you what Cordelia Cruise is like from inside, the cost of Cordelia Cruise, how to book, things to keep in mind and what's included in the cruise package. All in all, I think this cruise was great for a perfect family holiday!

Booked the cruise through: https://www.gtholidays.in (reach out to them on 9940882200)

title: Visiting DAWKI, Meghalaya (Near Bangladesh) & MAWLYNNONG Village (Cleanest Village in Asia) | Ep #2
description:
Hey everyone! I recently visited Meghalaya with my family and had the most fun time! During our trip to Meghalaya, we visited Shillong, Umiam Lake, places around Shillong, Cherrapunji/Sohra, Double Decker Root Bridge, Dawki, Mawlynnong, tons of waterfalls that Meghalaya is famous for, and Mawphlang Sacred Forest.

This is the second video in the series where we travel from Shillong to Sohra, and on the way visit Dawki - which is famous for it's crystal clear Umngot River, said to be one of the cleanest rivers in Asia and the cleanest river in India, and lies on the Bangladesh border, and Mawlynnong village, which was once awarded the title of the cleanest village in Asia. In Mawlynnong, we visited the Mawlynnong village, and also the single living root bridge, which was so breathtaking!

If you're planning a trip to Dawki, do consider visiting Shnongpdeng nearby which is a little less commercial and offers kayaking and other activities. We missed out on that on our trip, but boating in Dawki was so beautiful and the crystal clear water is such a unique sight to behold. Absolutely loved it!

Also, I've interchangeably used Sohra and Cherrapunji, but the actual name now is Sohra. Cherrapunji seems to be what it's more popularly known as though, so excuse me for saying Cherrapunji.

title: EXPLORING KOLKATA SOLO FOR THE FIRST TIME! | Kolkata Vlog | Kritika Goel
description:
Join my FREE YouTube Masterclass: https://bit.ly/38dS4o6
Check out my store: https://www.kritikagoelshop.com
Started 2020 by visiting the charming city of Kolkata. This was my first time visiting Kolkata, and I had such an incredible time exploring the City of Joy solo. I spent three days sightseeing in Kolkata and vlogged the whole experience for you. Since it was my first time here and I came quite unprepared, I wasn’t sure what all to see, but I managed to cover as much as I could in three days. I visited Princep Ghat, Park Street, Victoria Memorial, Kumortuli, took a metro ride, took a ride in the iconic yellow taxi of Kolkata, saw the tram, and went on an incredible walking tour through the culturally diverse neighbourhoods of Kolkata. I also tried some amazing food, the famous Bengali sweets (mishti doi and sandesh), a few cafes and restaurants around Park street and my favourite: puchkas! Also, in case you didn’t know, Kolkata (or Calcutta) was the capital of India during the British rule, and in Kolkata really felt like I had been transported back in time! I loved the vibe of the city.

title: WORLD’S LARGEST MANGROVE FOREST! Sunderbans National Park | Kritika Goel
description:
Join my FREE YouTube Masterclass: https://bit.ly/38dS4o6
Check out my store: https://www.kritikagoelshop.com
Recently got the chance to visit the magnificent Sunderbans National Park. In case you didn’t know, it’s the largest deltic region and mangrove forest in the world. I did a one night two day trip. I went solo but since it was with a group, I ended up making some friends. I had such an amazing time on this trip. The Sunderbans are so incredibly beautiful, and so was the village we stayed at. We also got to spot a lot of wildlife like spotted dears, wild boars, crocodiles, monitor lizards and different kinds of birds. All in all, it was quite an adventurous and exciting trip to the Sunderbans.

The new phone I'm using is the LG G8X ThinQ: http://bit.ly/LGG8X-In

This is the tour I did: http://bit.ly/2uQO8JV

title: SIKKIM VLOG | Exploring Changu/Tsomgo Lake, Khecheopalri Lake and more! - Vlog #3 | North East India
description:
Join my FREE YouTube Masterclass: https://bit.ly/38dS4o6
Check out my store: https://www.kritikagoelshop.com
Hey everyone! I recently went on a trip to Sikkim with my friend Shumnima (who is from Sikkim). This is the third vlog in my four part series of Sikkim. In this video, we explore places around Pelling, visit Khecheopalri Lake, Singshore Bridge (which is the second highest suspension bridge in Asia), go to a village called Uttarey, and witness the magnificent Kanchenjunga ranges from our room! Also, we went on a day trip to Changu / Tsomgo Lake, which was beyond beautiful, and dare I say it, seemed like the ‘Iceland of India’. Hope you enjoy this video :)

title: GERMANY VLOG 🇩🇪 Exploring FREIBURG im Breisgau | MY First Time in Germany! Vlog #2
description:
This is my first time in Germany! I explored the fairy tale town of Freiburg and loved every bit of it! Freiburg I’m Breisgau is a two hour train ride from Zurich and it lies in the Black Forest region of Germany, so there’s lots to see around Freiburg. In this video, I just walked around the old town of Freiburg which was super quaint, checked out the farmer’s market, walked up the bridge on the station, tried some beer, and tried the famous black forest cake :D One of the best things about Freiburg im Breisgau is that it's a green and sustainable city. In the next vlog, you’ll see me learn snow boarding and visiting a thermal bath in Freiburg :) Hope I get to visit Germany and Freiburg again someday!

description:

Hey guys, here’s part 4 of my travel series from Bali, which is the final video in this series, and in this video, I explore the stunning paradise island of Nusa Penida. I did a day trip to Nusa Penida from Seminyak and visited Kelingking Beach, Angel’s Billabong, Broken Beach, and Crystal Bay. I must admit, Nusa Penida is one of the most beautiful and untouched places I’ve ever been to and it’s totally worth visiting!
The best way to get to Nusa Penida is by taking a boat from Sanur in Bali (which is about 45-60 minutes from both Ubud and Seminyak).

title: SPACE POD EXPERIENCE | Singapore Capsule Hotel Tour: Rs. 2500 /Night!
description:
Join my FREE YouTube Masterclass: https://bit.ly/38dS4o6
Check out my store: https://www.kritikagoelshop.com
On my first night in Singapore, I decided to stay in a space pod to see what it’s like, and here’s a tour of the space capsule pod. I didn't know what to expect from a capsule hotel but this was quite an experience! The whole place gave me such a futuristic, Star Wars vibe and I couldn’t even imagine such a quirky accommodation to ever exist! Watch all the way till the end to know more about the price, lockers and storage, toilets, and other facilities. The one I stayed at is called MET A Space Pod and is in Boat Quay.

Booked on WEGO: https://wegotravel.onelink.me/cYro/CheapestFlightsxHotels 
→ Airbnb (Rs. 2,200 free travel credit): www.airbnb.co.in/c/kritikag38 

Capsule hotels are basically popular in Japan and other Asian countries and are a type of hotel that features a large number of small bed-sized rooms known as pods. Honestly, the pod turned out to be more spacious and comfortable than expected, and I had a really nice and comfortable stay. I didn’t feel claustrophobic at all (for everyone asking), and it also helped that the hostel was located in a really nice location (Boat Quay).

Highly recommend staying here just for the experience! It’s super cool. :D

title: SCHENGEN VISA FOR INDIANS | Documents Required, Cost & How to Apply for Europe Tourist Visa!
description:
If you’re looking to apply for a Schengen visa (tourist visa for Europe), then this video covers everything you need to know as an Indian applying for a Schengen visa in 2022. I cover what the Schengen visa is, different types of Schengen visa, how and where to apply, the list of documents you need to submit to get your visa, the visa fee for the Schengen visa, and I’ve also tried to answer some of the questions you guys sent me on Instagram and some general tips for the Schengen visa. This is my fourth time applying for a Schengen visa in four years, so hopefully, this information I’ve shared based on my experience with VFS and the Schengen visa is useful and if you have any more questions, let me know in the comments!

Join my group trip to Bali: https://trips.trovatrip.com/trips/bali-with-kritika-goel-sep-2022

Day 6: Spend the day at Aquaventure water park, evening exploring JBR
Day 7: Back to India

title: MADE IT TO GUWAHATI, ASSAM | Trying amazing food in Guwahati | Enroute Meghalaya!
description:
After almost a year of sitting at home, I finally went on my first official trip to the beautiful Meghalaya! This is the first video in this series, where I fly from Chennai to Guwahati in Assam and spent the day in Guwahati. We basically ended up eating a lot of good food in Guwahati - tried the street food, momos, chaat (special vada pav) in Fancy Bazaar, and an authentic Assamese thali in Guwahati. Although I wasn’t planning on making this video, I’m glad I did. I've also shared the guidelines to travel to Meghalaya right now and information on how I booked this trip! This is not the usual travel vlog, but more of a food vlog, however, so much more to come in my Meghalaya series! Stay tuned :)

✨ Follow me on Instagram for real time travel updates and behind the scenes: https://www.instagram.com/kritika_goel

title: EXPLORING SWITZERLAND | Indian Girl Traveling Solo in Switzerland! 🇨🇭
description:
To get €20/$20 off the deposit on Lingoda, use the code KRITIKA20 | Sign up for Lingoda here: https://try.lingoda.com/Sprint_Kritika

I spent four days in Switzerland back in December and here's a vlog of me exploring Switzerland. I originally had plans to spend a longer time in the country and do a lot more things, but due to the restrictions back then, I could only spend four days in Switzerland. Nevertheless, I had such an amazing time exploring Switzerland. Switzerland has always been a dream country for me to visit and it was beyond beautiful! I walked around the beautiful lanes of Zurich, took a train from Zurich to Zermatt where I witnessed some stunning snowy views of the Swiss Alps and the magnificent Matterhorn, took the Gornergrat Bahn to see the Matterhorn up close, went to Lausanne, Montreux, Cailler chocolate factory, and Gruyere to try out some delicious Swiss chocolate and fondue! It was incredible traveling solo in Switzerland and also reuniting with my high school friend after so long traveling with him! Hope you enjoy this vlog as much as I enjoyed my time in Switzerland :) Also, as mentioned in the vlog, I actually had the chance to go back to Switzerland a month and a half later and do everything I missed doing the first time around, so stay tuned for more vlogs from beautiful Switzerland! :)

title: NUSA PENIDA VLOG 🌴 My Favourite Spot in Nusa Penida | Bali with Subscribers Ep 3
description:
Hosted my first ever group trip with subscribers and traveled to Bali & Nusa Penida with 11 of my subscribers who joined me on an 8 day trip around Bali and Nusa Penida! In this vlog, you can see us exploring Nusa Penida. We visited my most favourite spot in Nusa Penida - Tembeling beach with a natural infinity pool and cave, had lunch at Amok Sunset with a stunning view, and visited Crystal Bay (we visited the more popular spots like Diamond Beach and Kelingking beach in the last vlog). Then took the ferry back to Sanur in Bali the next day where we all tried standup paddle boarding, did some shopping, an amazing Balinese spa, and some partying in Seminyak and La Favela. Can’t believe how quickly this trip to Bali ended but leaving with so many fond memories!

Thanks to TrovaTrip for helping me organize this trip, and to the amazing people who joined me on it! 

I have a group trip to Iceland open at the moment: https://www.trovatrip.com/trips/iceland-with-kritika-goel-jun-2023.html

title: PARIS to the NETHERLANDS *by train* | Indian Girl Traveling Solo in Europe!
description:
Hello from Europe! I'm on a one month long solo trip in Europe, and after spending 5 days in Paris, I took the Thalys fast train that goes from Paris to Amsterdam and headed to the Netherlands. I spent my morning soaking in Paris one last time; booked a photo walking tour for myself and got some nice photos with the Eiffel Tower and then headed to the train station to go from Paris to Eindhoven. title: MAHABALESHWAR VLOG | Luxury Weekend Staycation In Mahabaleshwar | Kritika Goel
description:
Join my FREE YouTube Masterclass: https://bit.ly/38dS4o6
Check out my store: https://www.kritikagoelshop.com
MY ONLINE STORE  ➭ https://sellfy.com/kritikagoel/
Instagram  ➭ https://www.instagram.com/kritikagoelpresets/

Recently did a weekend trip to Mahabaleshwar to explore and stay at the beautiful and luxurious property of Le Mèridien Mahabaleshwar Resort & Spa. Mahabaleshwar is a popular hill station in Maharashtra (the biggest in the state) and is a 6 hour drive from Mumbai. Spent two nights at the resort and throughly enjoyed my luxury staycation there. We ate some amazing food, did a trek to Helen’s Point and had a breakfast picnic in a tent, tried out a lot of strawberries (even went strawberry picking) and also managed to catch a few touristy spots like Mapro Garden and Parsi Point. So grateful for this incredible experience.

Huge thanks to Le Mèridien Mahabaleshwar Resort & Spa for hosting me and for the amazing hospitality. Had a wonderful stay there! :)

title: Travel With Me to the Maldives!
description:
TRAVEL WITH ME TO THE MALDIVES!  www.madovermaldives.com/kritika

So excited to launch my group trip to the beautiful Maldives with @madovermaldives which will happen between March 22nd and 26th (so you only have to take three days off from work)! This is going to be a completely offbeat and adventurous trip to the Maldives!

All details here: www.madovermaldives.com/kritika

The package cost is Rs. 69,000 + 5% GST + 5% TCS (refundable)

Here’s what’s included in this:

💙 4N/5D stay at Blue World, Dharavandhoo (on twin sharing basis) including 4 breakfasts, 4 dinners, and 1 BBQ lunch (Dharavndhoo is a local island of Baa Atoll with the beautiful Hanifaru Bay).

💙 Domestic round-trip flight in the Maldives from Male to Dharavandhoo and back.

💙 All activities including snorkeling at two points (snorkeling equipment included and there’ll also be a lesson in case its your first time), swimming with turtles, island hopping, sandbank visits, etc.

💙 All transfers throughout the trip.

The booking details and full itinerary here: www.madovermaldives.com/kritika 💙 

Mad excited to be working with @madovermaldives on this amazing and unique itinerary! They’re experts on the Maldives and have been making budget trips there for a while now so we’re in good hands!

You can book your spot now by paying just 20k (the balance payment will have to be made 30 days before the trip).

20 spots in total (mixed gender) and we only have a few more spots left right now 🥳 so head to the link above to book your spot and join me in the Maldives!

description:

title: Holi Photoshoot Ideas 🎨 #Shorts #Holi
description:
Happy Holi everyone! Here are some fun Holi photoshoot ideas for you in 15 seconds! Had an impromptu Holi at home and spoke about it on my Instagram (https://www.instagram.com/kritika_goel​), sharing my thoughts below :)

Growing up, Holi was my favorite festival but my version of Holi was very different from what you’ve probably grown up with. Here in South India, Holi isn’t really celebrated, in fact we didn’t even get a day off from school on Holi. I don’t think Holi colors were even sold here, and for context, I didn’t even know what a pichkari was until I got a little older. 😅
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So what we’d do instead was that on the Holi weekend, my family and a few close friends would get together, have buckets of colored water (thanks to my mom getting creative with food color 😃) and have the most fun time splashing water on each other. That’s Holi for me, just goofing around and having fun with family (and of course, taking photos haha). 🤗
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
So much has changed since then but Holi has still remained this low key yet fun time with family. Hope you’re all celebrating at home with the people you love (please don’t head out given the times we’re in 🙈). Happy Holi to you and your family! 💛🌈

title: BRNO, CZECH REPUBLIC - I Didn’t Expect BRNO to be THIS beautiful! 🏰 Vlog #3
description:
Join my FREE YouTube Masterclass: https://bit.ly/38dS4o6
Check out my store: https://www.kritikagoelshop.com
I went on a week long trip to Czech Republic in the month of August and here’s the third and final vlog from my trip! ❤️ I did this trip with the tourism board of Czech Republic and it was such a memorable one! In this video, you’ll see we exploring cities in South Moravia - basically Brno and Mikulov. Brno is the second largest city in Czech, and was without a doubt my most favourite city in Czech Republic, and if you watched this video, you’ll know why - it literally looks like a fairytale land!
😍

In Brno, we explored Špilberk Castle, the Cathedral, the main square and a ton of cute spots. We also got a chance to check out a few concerts because we visited during the time of Brno Music Marathon. We ended out trip in the cute town of Mikulov, and explored some vineyards along the way! Also got to see glimpses of Vienna in Austria because our flight back from was from there.

A huge thanks to Czech Tourism for taking me on this trip! ❤️

Don’t forget to follow me on Instagram for some live updates from my trips: https://www.instagram.com/kritika_goel

description:

Check out my store: https://www.kritikagoelshop.com
A DAY AT UNIVERSAL STUDIOS SINGAPORE | Went to an amusement park ALONE!

In today’s vlog, I spend a day exploring and chilling at Universal Studios Singapore all by myself. I’ve never been to an amusement park alone before but this was quite an experience! Literally went on every ride and made a friend as well! :D
Also took full advantage of being solo by using the single rider line and not having to wait in long queues so that was awesome! I think my favorite rides were the Mummy ride and the Transformers one.
I also ended up exploring Sentosa Island a bit, watched the  laser show, the light and sound show called Crane Dhow, and the Merlion. Super fun day overall!

title: SKYDIVING IN SWITZERLAND!🇨🇭 | Most Beautiful Skydiving Experience in Interlaken, Switzerland Ep #4
description:
My second time skydiving and what better spot than Interlaken Switzerland, where I did skydiving in the middle of the beautiful Swiss Alps! In this video, I go from Zurich to Interlaken by train, explore the town of Interlaken which lies between two lakes, and the highlight of my trip - skydiving in Interlaken! I never imagined I’d go skydiving twice, that too in Switzerland on a solo trip, and in the winter, but it was one of the most beautiful experiences of my life! If you’re planning a trip to Switzerland and specifically to Interlaken, definitely experience skydiving in Interlaken!

title: SWITZERLAND'S MOST BEAUTIFUL CITY 🇨🇭 Day Trip to Lucerne & Mount Rigi (Paradise on Earth!)
description:
Ended my trip to Switzerland with a day trip to Lucerne and Mount Rigi from Zurich! The top of Rigi was the most wind I’ve ever experienced in life 😅 but overall, it turned out to be such a spectacular day with some stunning views. I did a day trip to Mount Rigi from Zurich (in February 2022) where I went on top of Rigi Kulm, hiked a bit in the snow, took a beautiful train down to Vitznau by Lake Lucerne from where I took a boat to Lucerne and explored the city by night! Also, I was actually with a friend of mine who was too shy to be on camera but in case you were wondering who took some of my shots, it was him! We had some delicious raclette at night, and let’s just say it’s become one of my favourite dishes! :D Hope you enjoy this vlog from Switzerland’s most beautiful city - Lucerne :)

The Eurail pass I got: https://www.eurail.com/en/eurail-passes/bestseller-10-days

title: Trekking to Double Decker Living Root Bridge in Sohra (Cherrapunji) | Meghalaya Vlog Ep #3
description:
Hey everyone! I recently visited Meghalaya with my family and had the most fun time! During our trip to Meghalaya, we visited Shillong, Umiam Lake, places around Shillong, Cherrapunji/Sohra, Double Decker Root Bridge, Dawki, Mawlynnong, tons of waterfalls, and Mawphlong Sacred Forest.

This is the third vlog from my Meghalaya series and in this video, we trekked to the Double Decker Living Root bridge in Sohra / Cherrapunjee. This trek involves going down 3500 steps and coming back up 3500 steps so it was quite intense and I wouldn’t recommend it for elderly people or for someone who has knee issues. But having said that, this was such a FUN day and seeing the double decker root bridge was totally worth the hike!

Sohra is one of the wettest places on the planet, and home to a lot of living root bridges. The one we visited in this video  is The Double Decker Living Root Bridge in Nongriat Village, and as you can see, it has two levels to it.

While it's possible to trek to the Double Decker Root Bridge in one day, if you have the time, I recommend spending a night here in Nongriat Village (there are a few homestays there), and also visit Rainbow Falls (which are an hour or so away from here by walk). There’s also a Blue Lagoon which we missed seeing so you could try covering that too. But overall, this trek was a great experience, and the highlight for me was swimming in the water near the Double Decker Living Root Bridge. Totally worth visiting this place if you’re planning a trip to Meghalaya and Sohra/Cherrapunjee.

title: MALDIVES TRAVEL VLOG 🏝️ Snorkeling, Diving, & Exploring Maldives with my Subscribers! 🤩
description:
Visited the Maldives with my subscribers; we were at a local island called Dharavandhu in Hanifaru Bay in the Maldives and here’s a travel vlog from my trip there. I hosted a group trip to the Maldives where some of my subscribers joined me. We had the most amazing few days there snorkeling, scuba diving, seeing sharks and sting rays swim at the beach, visiting a beautiful sandbank, swimming with turtles, seeing the most beautiful sunsets, and even some bioluminescence. This was my first time exploring a local island in the Maldives and it was quite a contrasting yet amazing experience compared to staying on a resort island.

In case you’re wondering, the cost of this trip was Rs. 69,000 (including domestic flights but excluding intentional flights), so visiting a local island in the Maldives is way more budget-friendly and affordable compared to resort islands.

title: Making Vegetarian Baos at Home | Easy Steamed Bao Buns Recipe | Cooking with Mom
description:
Mom and I made vegetarian baos at home and here’s a fun vlog from that whole experience! We made vegetarian (eggless) steamed baos which turned out super soft and fluffy, a chilli paneer stuffing, and a peanut sauce to go with it, and these veg baos turned out soooo delicious! If you try making these baos at home, the recipe is down below :)

————————————

🍴RECIPE🍴

BAOS:
1. Mix 3/4th tablespoon active dry yeast, 1 tablespoon sugar, and 3/4th cup lukewarm water and leave it aside for approx 10 mins till the yeast activates.
2. In a large bowl, mix 3.5 cups maida, 1.5 teaspoon baking powder, 1.5 tbs sugar and 1/4th teaspoon salt. Mix well.
3. Add to this, the yeast water, 3/4th cup warm milk, and 3 tbs oil (any edible oil works).
4. Combine everything and knead the dough on a flat surface for 6-7 minutes till it becomes smooth. Add more flour if it is very sticky, or a little bit of water if it is very dry.
5. Keep this aside for one and a half hour covered with a wet cloth, till your dough doubles in size. (You can keep it in a warm place for faster proofing)
6. When it’s done, punch the dough down again and knead for 5 mins to remove air bubbles.
7. Roll out the dough into 1 cm thick circle and approx 3 inch diameter and apply some oil, fold it, press slightly in the middle, place it on a banana leaf/parchment paper, cover them with a damp cloth, and keep aside for 30 minutes for second proofing.
8. Once they have risen, you can steam them in an idli steamer for 12-13 minutes, and your baos will be ready.

CHILLI PANEER STUFFING:
1. Deseed 15 Kashmiri chilis and soak them in hot water for half an hour. Discard the water and blend the chilis smooth.
2. Heat 3 tbs oil in a pan, add 10 tbs finely chopped garlic, 2 teaspoons grated ginger, and sauté for 2 minutes to allow the raw smell to go (don’t brown it).
3. Add the chilli paste and cook till the oil separates for about 5 minutes. Remove this paste into a container and keep it aside.
4. In the same pan, add 2 tablespoon oil, 1.5 cups chopped onion and sauté till translucent.
5. Add 1 cup chopped green capsicum, and sauté for another 2 minutes on medium flame.
6. Add the pre-cooked paste that we made to this and mix well for another 2 minutes.
7. Add 5 tablespoon light soy sauce (or 2.5 tbs regular soy sauce), 3 tbs tomato ketchup, and 2 teaspoons chilli sauce, 1 teaspoon brown sugar (regular sugar is fine too), some salt and pepper to taste. Stir this well.
8. Mix 4 teaspoons of cornflour in a separate bowl with a cup of water to make a thin slurry, add this slurry to the pan with everything we made so far, and allow it to simmer till we get a thick sauce (for about 5 minutes).
9. Add cubed paneer (1/2 kg paneer), and gently toss till the pieces are coated completely.
10. Remove from the flame and add chopped spring onions for garnishing.

Place this paneer filling in the opening of the bao and garnish with carrot, cucumbers, spring onions and roasted sesame seeds, and serve with peanut sauce.

PEANUT SAUCE:
Blend the following ingredients in a mixer to a smooth sauce:
1. Roasted peanuts - 1/2 cup
2. 2 flakes of garlic
3. Roasted sesame - 2 tablespoon
4. Tamarind paste - 1 tablespoon
5. Jaggery - 1 tablespoon
6. Salt to taste
7. Kashmiri red chilli powder - 1 teaspoon
8. Soy sauce - 1.5 tablespoon
9. Water - 1/2 cup or as required

title: DAY TRIP TO ABU DHABI | Riding the World’s Fastest Rollercoaster at FERRARI WORLD | Kritika Goel
description:
Join my FREE YouTube Masterclass: https://bit.ly/38dS4o6
Check out my store: https://www.kritikagoelshop.com
Day 5 of my family vacation to Dubai was spent doing a day trip to Abu Dhabi. Abu Dhabi is the capital of UAE, and is about two hours away from Dubai. We spent the day exploring the stunning Grand Mosque, which is one of the major highlights of Abu Dhabi, and the other half of the day at Ferrari World. We went on the world’s fastest roller coaster, which was EPIC, the world’s tallest loop rollercoaster and a few other awesome rides. Overall it was a fun day trip to Abu Dhabi.

title: TRAVELING TO BALI WITH MY SUBSCRIBERS | Bali Travel Vlog Ep 1: UBUD!
description:
Hosted my first ever group trip with subscribers and traveled to Bali with 11 of my subscribers who joined me on an 8 day trip around Bali and Nusa Penida! In this vlog, you can see us exploring Ubud, visiting some of the famous temples in the area, the Tegalalang rice terraces where we went on the Bali swing, the Sacred Monkey Forest, Campuhan Ridge Walk, tried some delicious local food, and did a coffee workshop! Loved this whole group trip experience and I hope to host more such group trips each year! Thanks to TrovaTrip for helping me organize this trip, and to the amazing people who joined me on it! 

I have a group trip to Iceland open at the moment: https://www.trovatrip.com/trips/iceland-with-kritika-goel-jun-2023.html

title: MALAGA TRAVEL VLOG | Indian Girl Traveling Solo in Spain! 🇪🇸
description:
Did a solo trip to Spain a while bag and started with the beautiful and vibrant city of Malaga in the south of Spain in Andalusia. I spent three days in Malaga in the month of December and during my time there, I visited the Malaga Cathedral, the Alcazaba, ate a lot of good food, saw lots of light shows, went to Malagueta beach, the pier, and a lot more! Had such a memorable time in Malaga and hope I get to visit the south of Spain again someday! 

Where I stayed in Malaga: https://www.booking.com/hotel/es/residencia-unoversitaria-san-jose.en-gb.html?aid=1664544&label=postbooking_confemail&sid=fa09cb1e890351c91bc4a0a91aa95f7d&dist=0&keep_landing=1&sb_price_type=total&type=total& (not that great to be honest, I couldn't find anything else that weekend)
Picasso Museum tickets: https://www.getyourguide.com/picasso-museum-malaga-l5011/museo-picasso-malaga-permanent-collection-t32477/ (you get 10% off on GetYourGuide with a Eurail pass)

title: OLD DUBAI AND DESERT SAFARI: Dune Bashing, Quad Biking and Belly Dancing! 🐪 | Kritika Goel
description:
Join my FREE YouTube Masterclass: https://bit.ly/38dS4o6
Check out my store: https://www.kritikagoelshop.com
Hey guys! Here’s the third vlog from my recent trip to Dubai with my family! I’m so excited to be sharing these Dubai vlogs with you because they’re more raw, personal and fun! In this vlog, we explore Old Dubai, the spice souk (where we ended up doing a lot of shopping), took an abra ride, visited the Old Dubai Souq, and then went on an exciting desert safari with dune bashing, quad biking, belly dancing and a cool fire show! Also, we're staying in the world's tallest hotel (Hotel Gevora) with the most epic pool, so ended our day by unwinding there. All-in-all a very fun day! Super excited about tomorrow’s vlog though! Stay tuned. :)

title: NUSA PENIDA VLOG (The Most Beautiful Island in Bali!) | Bali Travel Vlog Ep 2: Nusa Penida! 🌊
description:
Check out THE LÄND: https://bit.ly/THELAEND_KritikaGoel

Hosted my first-ever group trip with subscribers and traveled to Bali and with 11 of my subscribers who joined me on an 8 day trip around Bali and Nusa Penida! In this vlog, you can see us exploring the most beautiful island of Bali - Nusa Penida. We spent 3 days there exploring all the famous spots - Diamond Beach, Rumah Pohon Tree House, Atuh Beach, Kelingking Beach, Broken Beach, Angel's Billabong, Crystal Bay, and more! We also went snorkeling in Nusa Penida, and overall had such an amazing time!

description:
Join my FREE YouTube Masterclass: https://bit.ly/38dS4o6

I recently had the chance to explore Hong Kong with Hong Kong Tourism Board and Tripoto, and I vlogged the whole experience! This is my second vlog from the trip and in this video, I take the super cool cable car (with a glass bottom) to visit the Big Buddha in Lantau Island, go to the second highest bar in the world, go shopping at the Ladies Market, learn stand up paddle boarding in Sai Kung, eat food at Michelin star restaurants, learn to make dim sums, and visit the Victoria Peak for some stunning views of the city. All this and more! :)

If you’re planning a trip to Hong Kong, I hope my vlog series will help you plan your itinerary! 🤗 Hope you enjoy this video! ❤️

title: 48 Hours INSIDE San Francisco International Airport! ✈️ Behind-the-Scenes & Sustainability at SFO
description:
Spent 48 hours inside San Francisco International Airport and in this travel vlog, I take you behind the scenes with me and show you not only all the fun things you can do at SFO but also some of the sustainability measures they’re taking at the airport. This airport has an observation deck for plane spotting, yoga rooms to relax, the Wag Brigade with the cutest animals you can pet and play with, tons of eating options, a five-star hotel on the airport premise, and TONS more! In this vlog, we also see how the airport is doing its bit to be more sustainable, how they manage their waste and treat their own water, and also see sustainable aviation fuel live in action.

You can read more about sustainability at SFO here: https://www.flysfo.com/about/sustainability 

Huge thanks to San Francisco International Airport for inviting me and giving me behind-the-scenes access to the airport! It was such an incredible experience :)

title: Beautiful Waterfalls & Caves in SOHRA, MEGHALAYA (Cherrapunji) | Police Bazaar in SHILLONG | Ep #4
description:
Hey everyone! I recently visited Meghalaya with my family and had the most fun time! During our trip to Meghalaya, we visited Shillong, Umiam Lake, places around Shillong, Cherrapunji/Sohra, tons of waterfalls and even a cave, Double Decker Root Bridge, Dawki, Mawlynnong, tons of waterfalls, and Mawphlang Sacred Forest.

This is the fourth vlog from my Meghalaya series and in this video, we explored the famous caves and waterfalls around Sohra Cherrapunji. Unfortunately, since we visited in March, Dainthlen Falls, Seven Sister falls and Nohkhalikai falls were mostly dried up but I absolutely loved Wei Sawdong Waterfalls and Elephant Falls. Also, Mawsmai cave was one of the highlights of the day for sure, such a mysterious cave with limestones. We also, drove down from Sohra to Shillong in Meghalaya and spent the evening exploring the famous Police Bazaar in Shillong and the food culture of Shillong. Hope you enjoy this vlog of me exploring waterfalls & caves in Sohra, Meghalaya!

title: Switzerland’s Most Scenic Train Ride (Glacier Express)! 😍 #Shorts
description:
I went on the first class Glacier Express from Zermatt to St. Moritz (in the month of February) and it was one of the most scenic train journeys I have ever experienced, and not just in Switzerland. 😍 It’s an 8 hour long train ride between St. Moritz and Zermatt and is known to be Switzerland’s most luxurious and expensive train rides. You get panoramic views of the Swiss Alps! 🏔❤️

Watch the full vlog here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y-NjAVmaVVo

It has three different classes: Excellence class, first class, and second class and the prices vary depending on which class you’re in, the season and whether you’re doing the whole journey or only a part of it.

Here are the prices (approx since currency exchange keeps changing):
Second class: Rs. 15,000
First class: Rs. 25,000
Excellence class: Rs. 52,000
Yup, it’s quite expensive! 😅🤑

However, the cool part is the first and second classes are included in the Eurail pass (you just need to pay 40 franks extra to reserve your seat) so that’s what I did since I had a @eurail pass anyway for all my train rides! So this works out to be more cost effective if you’re planning a lot of train rides on your trip to Europe.

They also serve food (at an extra cost for first and second class), but you can also carry your own (which is what I did 😋).

Would you add this to your bucket list? Full vlog from here on my YouTube channel! 🤗
.

.

title: SAN FRANCISCO TRAVEL VLOG 🇺🇸 Indian Girl Traveling Solo in San Francisco, USA | Kritika Goel
description:
Explored San Francisco solo and even though it was my second time here, I absolutely loved the city! In this travel vlog, I spent 3 days in San Francisco, and show you some of the best things to do in San Francisco. I explored Chinatown, Dogpatch, the Golden Gate Bridge, some museums in SF, the Fisherman’s Wharf, the Ferry Building, rode the iconic cable cars of San Francisco, and SF MoMA. One of the highlights was the sunset cruise that goes under the Golden Gate Bridge and has some stunning views of the city! Also ate some delicious food while I was there!

Huge thanks to SF Travel for sponsoring my time in San Francisco and putting together an amazing itinerary!

title: India's Grand Canyon in Meghalaya! | Our Last Day in Shillong - Laitlum Grand Canyon | Ep #6
description:
Hey everyone! I recently visited Meghalaya with my family and had the most fun time! During our trip to Meghalaya, we visited Shillong, Umiam Lake, places around Shillong, Cherrapunji/Sohra, tons of waterfalls and even a cave, Double Decker Root Bridge, Dawki, Mawlynnong, tons of waterfalls, Laitlum Grand Canyon and Mawphlang Sacred Forest.

This is the sixth and last vlog from my Meghalaya series and in this video, we explored the majestic Laitlum Grand Canyon, which is an hour and a half away from Shillong. The term Laitlum translates to 'end of hills' and the place totally does justice to its name! The views from Laitlum Canyon were spectacular and Laitlum should totally be on your list of places to visit in Meghalaya! We also explored a bit of Shillong - Don Bosco Museum to be specific. And finally ended the day in our hotel at Laitumkhrah, Shillong. We also visited the magnificent Umiam Lake the next morning on our way back to Guwahati. This was such an amazing trip and I'm so glad I got to visit Meghalaya with my family :)

✨ Follow me on Instagram for real time travel updates and behind the scenes: https://www.instagram.com/kritika_goel 

✨ The whole Meghalaya vlog was shot on my Canon M50 mark ii: https://amzn.to/3vRJSVv and my iPhone 12 Pro Max

title: Access Airport Lounges for FREE (international and domestic)! #Shorts
description:
If you’ve ever wondered how I keep going to airport lounges all around the world (without actually paying extra for it), then here’s how! ✈️

A lot of credit cards offer something called the Priority Pass complimentary along with your card (some have limited visits and the more premium cards offer unlimited lounge access). You can pay and buy the Priority Pass too (last time I checked, the unlimited one was for around $350-$400 per year), but you can get it complimentary along with some credit cards.

A few of that I know offer the Priority Pass are:
1. HDFC Infinia
2. Citi Prestige
3. HDFC Regalia (limited)
4. HDFC Regalia First (limited)
5. Axis Privilege
6. Yes First Exclusive
7. ICICI Sapphiro
8. HDFC Diners Black (no Priority Pass but offers lounge access around the world)
and many more! So do some research to figure out what card you’re eligible for and get that free lounge access! 😃

Apart from this, a lot of debit and credit cards also let you access domestic lounges in India. I didn’t know my debit card gave me lounge access for a good 4-5 years of having it so check online/with your bank to see if they offer lounge access.

Access to airport lounges is great to have, especially if you travel frequently. They usually have free food and drinks, good WiFi, comfortable seating with charging ports, newspapers/magazines, and usually a great view! 😍

I get asked this SOOO often, so hope this helps! Share if you found this useful 😊
